        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 5:49PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 549 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 7 miles southwest of Garden City, moving north at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Big Spring, Garden City, Coahoma, Forsan, Sand Springs, Lomax, Big
Spring Country Club, Big Spring McMahon-Wrinkle Airpark, Saint
Lawrence, and Elbow.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 167 and 195.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
